<paragraph id="8BB7368AD867FFE83CB4FCE931B7F8E3" blockId="50.[151,1058,850,901]" pageId="50" pageNumber="1009">
E t y m o l o g y: The trivial name, 
<emphasis id="B97CEA98D867FFE83E3EFCE830BAF801" box="[541,645,850,871]" italics="true" pageId="50" pageNumber="1009">erudiatum</emphasis>
, is a Latin name that stems from 
<emphasis id="B97CEA98D867FFE83FC3FCE8361DF801" box="[992,1058,850,871]" italics="true" pageId="50" pageNumber="1009">erudio</emphasis>
(= polish); with reference to the polished posterior 1/3 
<superScript id="7C7D9BC2D867FFE83E9FFCD130F6F81F" attach="left" box="[700,713,875,889]" fontSize="6" pageId="50" pageNumber="1009">rd</superScript>
of the elytral disc.
</paragraph>
